edu.umn.biomedicus.uima.migration

Interface TypeSystemMigration


  • public TypeSystemMigration

    Performs a type system migration between two different UIMA type systems by converting XMI files.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods

      • deleteByDefault

        boolean deleteByDefault()

        Decides whether the migration should copy over, or delete types by default.

        Returns:
        implement this to return false if you want feature structures to be copied by default, or return true if you want types to be deleted by default.

      • typesNotDefaulted

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> typesNotDefaulted()

        A list of the types where the default action is not taken. If the default action is to delete, these types will be copied to the new view. If the default action is to copy, these types will be deleted.

        Returns:
        list of qualified UIMA type names where the default action is not taken
        See Also:
        TypeSystemMigration.deleteByDefault
